                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-description"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} is a cheerful, bright-eyed 5-year-old girl who arrives at the pediatric clinic accompanied by her mother. She is dressed in a pink sweater adorned with small stars, though today she looks notably tired and less animated than usual. Her cheeks are flushed, her nose is red and runny, and she occasionally rubs her eyes. She sniffles repeatedly and winces when she swallows, tugging at her throat with her small hand. Her voice is slightly hoarse, and she produces a dry, barky cough every few minutes.\n\n{patientName} attends kindergarten five days a week, where she loves painting, building blocks, and chasing her classmates during outdoor play. Her mother mentions that several children in her class have been sent home sick with similar symptoms over the past two weeks. At home, {patientName} lives with both parents and her 8-year-old brother, who recovered from a cold just last week. She has a pet hamster named \"Fluffy\" that she adores.\n\nOver the past three days, {patientName} has had a fever peaking at 38.7°C, a sore throat, nasal congestion, and a mild headache. She has been eating poorly and drinking less than usual. She slept restlessly the night before the visit, waking twice crying from discomfort. Her mother reports no vomiting, diarrhea, rash, or difficulty breathing.\n\n{patientName} is generally a healthy and active child who enjoys swimming lessons on Saturday mornings and watching animated movies with her family. She eats a varied diet — though she particularly loves macaroni and cheese — and usually sleeps 10–11 hours per night. Her immunizations are up to date according to the national schedule."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:0cb50ccc-22fa-4f16-a047-bdb77aecf6e8",
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Communication",
        "status": "completed",
